<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468676>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Catamicrophyllum caucasicum (Attems, 1901), ♁ from Nakhichevan (ZMUM). A. Left gonopods, lateral view. B. Right gonopods, mesal view. C. Distal part of hamulus, mesal view. Abbreviations: h: hamulus, l: intermediate lamella, M: mesomere, O: opisthomere, P: promere, pl: posterior lobe, t: terminal process. Scale bars: 0.3 mm (A, B), 0.05 mm (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468678>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Slenderness of body of males of Catamicrophyllum caucasicum (Attems, 1901) (x: data of Enghoff (1995); +: present data) and Catamicrophyllum beroni sp. nov. (o) expressed as relation of vertical diameter to number of body rings." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

